## Domain Setup

### Default
Your app will be at: `project-name.vercel.app`

### Custom Domain
1. Vercel Dashboard → Settings → Domains
2. Add your domain
3. Configure DNS records as shown
4. Update `NEXTAUTH_URL` to new domain
5. Add new redirect URI in Spotify Dashboard

## Preview Deployments

Every PR gets a preview URL automatically.

⚠️ Preview deployments use the same env vars, so Spotify auth will work, but:
- Preview URLs are temporary
- They're not in Spotify's allowed redirect URIs

For PR previews to work with auth:
1. Add a wildcard redirect URI in Spotify (not recommended for production)
2. Or just test auth on main branch

## Monitoring

### Vercel Analytics (Built-in)
Enable in Vercel Dashboard → Analytics

### Error Tracking
Consider adding Sentry for production:

```bash
npm install @sentry/nextjs
```

## Performance Optimization

### Already Optimized by Next.js
- Automatic code splitting
- Image optimization
- Font optimization
- Static generation where possible

### Manual Optimizations
- Use dynamic imports for heavy D3 visualizations
- Lazy load non-critical components

```tsx
import dynamic from 'next/dynamic';

const GalaxyMode = dynamic(
  () => import('@/components/visualizer/GalaxyMode'),
  { loading: () => <Skeleton /> }
);
```

## Common Deployment Issues

### "Module not found"
- Check import paths use `@/` alias
- Ensure file names match exactly (case-sensitive)

### "Environment variable not found"
- Add to Vercel Dashboard, not just `.env.local`
- Redeploy after adding variables

### "NEXTAUTH_URL mismatch"
- Must match actual deployment URL exactly
- Include `https://`
- No trailing slash

### "Spotify redirect_uri mismatch"
- Add exact callback URL to Spotify Dashboard
- Format: `https://your-domain.vercel.app/api/auth/callback/spotify`

## CI/CD with GitHub Actions (Optional)

```yaml
# .github/workflows/ci.yml
name: CI

on:
  push:
    branches: [main]
  pull_request:
    branches: [main]

jobs:
  build:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - uses: actions/setup-node@v4
        with:
          node-version: '20'
          cache: 'npm'
      - run: npm ci
      - run: npm run lint
      - run: npm run build
      - run: npm test
```

## Post-Deploy Verification

1. Visit production URL
2. Click "Connect Spotify"
3. Complete OAuth flow
4. Verify visualization appears
5. Test all 4 modes
6. Check error states (pause music, private session)
